ames Lasdun","r2ContributorId":"26593","type":"contributor","bio":"<p>James Lasdun has published three books of poetry, two collections of short stories and most recently, a novel, The Horned Man. His story The Siege was adapted by Bernardo Bertolucci for his film Besieged, and is included in a selection of his stories under the same title. He co-wrote the screenplay for the films Signs and Wonders, and Sunday (based on another of his stories) which won Best Feature and Best Screenplay awards at Sundance, 1997. With Michael Hofmann he co-edited the anthology After Ovid: New Metamorphoses. He is the recipient of a Guggenheim Fellowship in poetry, and currently teaches a fiction workshop at Princeton.</p>","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/profile/jameslasdun","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/profile/jameslasdun","references":[]},{"id":"books/thrillers","webTitle":"Thrillers","type":"keyword","sectionId":"books","sectionName":"Books","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/books/thrillers","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/books/thrillers","references":[]},{"id":"type/article","webTitle":"Article","type":"type","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/articles","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/type/article","references":[]},{"id":"publication/theguardian","webTitle":"The Guardian","type":"publication","sectionId":"theguardian","sectionName":"From the Guardian","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/theguardian/all","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/publication/theguardian","references":[]}],"references":[],"elements":[{"id":"gu-image-432847348","relation":"main","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","mimeType":"image/jpeg","file":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Books/Pix/pictures/2014/3/24/1395663165702/Student-Protesters-in-Tia-001.jpg","typeData":{"source":"  Peter Turnley/CORBIS","photographer":"Peter Turnley","altText":"Student Protesters in Tiananmen Square","height":"54","credit":"Peter Turnley/  Peter Turn