 rate. I've rewritten it a dozen times since then.\"</p><p>Anyway, it's a cracker.</p><p><blockquote>She woke with a gasp, not knowing who she was, or where,\" writes Martin, from the perspective of a new character called Mercy. \"The smell of blood was heavy in her nostrils … or was that her nightmare, lingering? She had dreamed of wolves again, of running through some dark pine forest with a great pack at her hells, hard on the scent of prey.</blockquote></p><p>I don't want to give anything away, as the twist is far too enjoyable to spoil. <a href=\"http://www.georgerrmartin.com/excerpt-from-the-winds-of-winter\" title=\"\">Go and read it</a>, and come back and tell me what you think.</p><p>There's no confirmed release date, as yet, for the novel The Winds of Winter – it's keenly awaited, however, and there's <a href=\"http://www.windsofwinterrelease.com\" title=\"\">even a site dedicated to speculating about when it'll be published</a> (most recent hunch: \"I'm feeling confident that The Winds of Winter will be released in October (maybe November), 2015. The stars just seem to be aligning right for this one. GRRM has been quiet, which means he is writing. Fewer promotional tours and conferences, more writing. If he continues to spend his time in New Mexico, he could easily complete the book by year's end and start the final editing and promotional process for a fall release.\")</p><p>But at Martin's publisher, HarperCollins, his publisher Jane Johnson tells me this morning that there's no date lined up \"until George delivers, and I have no idea when that will be. This is such a huge series and so convoluted and hard to structure as he approaches the end that it is going to take time to get exactly right.\"</p><p>Ah well. Harness the excitement, Flood. For now, I'm going back for a reread of Mercy, and reminding myself, a la Neil Gaiman, that <a href=\"http://journal.neilgaiman.com/2009/05/entitlement-issues.html\" title=\"\">Martin is not my bitch</a>. And at least there's the new HBO series to look forward to, in the meantime.</p>","headline":"George RR Martin releases new chapter of The Winds of Winter","trailText":"Ahead of the new season of Games of Thrones on TV, the author has published an unseen chapter from the 6th book in the A Song of Fire and Ice series online – and it's a cracker, says<strong> Alison Flood</strong>","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/3/27/1395919207887/Game-Of-Thrones---2013-001.jpg","wordcount":"475","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-04-03T09:53:00Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/books/booksblog/2014/mar/27/george-rr-martin-new-chapter-the-winds-of-winter","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/books/booksblog/2014/mar/27/george-rr-martin-new-chapter-the-winds-of-winter","tags":[{"id":"books/booksblog","webTitle":"Books blog","type":"blog","sectionId":"books","sectionName":"Books","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/books/booksblog","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/books/booksblog","references":[]},{"id":"books/books","webTitle":"Books","type":"keyword","sectionId":"books","sectionName":"Books","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/books/books","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/books/books","references":[]},{"id":"culture/culture","webTitle":"Culture","type":"keyword","sectionId":"culture","sectionName":"Culture","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/culture/culture","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/culture/culture","references":[]},{"id":"books/george-rr-martin","webTitle":"George RR Martin","type":"keyword","sectionId":"books","sectionName":"Books","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/books/george-rr-martin","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/books/george-rr-martin","references":[]},{"id":"tv-and-radio/game-of-thrones","webTitle":"Game of Thrones","type":"keyword","sectionId":"tv-and-radio","sectionName":"Television &amp; radio","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/tv