n the Middle East, reporting from Iraq before, during and after the war of 2003. He has specialised in conflict, terrorism and Islamic militancy.</p><p>Currently based in New Delhi, he covers a wide range of social, political and cultural topics across South Asia. He is a regular commentator on television and radio.</p><p>Burke is the author of Al-Qaeda: the True Story of Radical Islam, published in 2003, which analysed the role of the militant group and its ideology and described the complex reality of modern Islamic radicalism. A second book, On The Road to Kandahar, was published in 2006. Burke speaks good French, average Hindi and Urdu and terrible Arabic.</p>","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/profile/jasonburke","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/profile/jasonburke","references":[]},{"id":"tone/reviews","webTitle":"Reviews","type":"tone","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/tone/reviews","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/tone/reviews","references":[]},{"id":"theobserver/new-review/books","webTitle":"Books","type":"newspaper-book-section","sectionId":"books","sectionName":"Books","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/theobserver/new-review/books","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/theobserver/new-review/books","references":[]},{"id":"theobserver/new-review","webTitle":"The New Review","type":"newspaper-book","sectionId":"culture","sectionName":"Culture","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/theobserver/new-review","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/theobserver/new-review","references":[]},{"id":"publication/theobserver","webTitle":"The Observer","type":"publication","sectionId":"theobserver","sectionName":"From the Observer","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/theobserver/all","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/publication/theobserver","references":[]},{"id":"global-development/global-development","webTitle":"Global development","type":"keyword","sectionId":"global-development","sectionName":"Global